<topic id="preferences-author-mathml" >
  <title>MathML Preferences</title>
  <body>
    <p>To configure the <term>MathML</term> editor of the <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode, go to
        <menucascade product="author editor">
        <uicontrol>Options</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> Preferences</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> Edit modes</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> Author</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> MathML</uicontrol>
      </menucascade><menucascade product="authorEclipse editorEclipse">
        <uicontrol>Window</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> Preferences</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> &lt;oXygen/></uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> Editor</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> Edit Modes / Pages</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> Author</uicontrol>
        <uicontrol> MathML</uicontrol>
      </menucascade>. You can configure the following parameters:</p>
    <dl>
      <dlentry>
        <dt><uicontrol>Equation minimum font size</uicontrol></dt>
        <dd>The minimum size of the font used for rendering mathematical symbols.</dd>
      </dlentry>
      <dlentry>
        <dt><uicontrol>MathFlow installation directory</uicontrol></dt>
        <dd>The installation folder where<ph keyref="product"/> looks for <term>MathFlow</term>
          Components (the <term>MathFlow</term> SDK).</dd>
      </dlentry>
      <dlentry>
        <dt><uicontrol>MathFlow license file</uicontrol></dt>
        <dd>The license for<term>MathFlow</term> Components (the <term>MathFlow</term> SDK).</dd>
      </dlentry>
      <dlentry>
        <dt><uicontrol>MathFlow preferred editor</uicontrol></dt>
        <dd>A<term>MathML</term> formula can be edited in one of three editors of the
            <term>MathFlow</term> Components (<term>MathFlow</term> SDK): structure editor, style
          editor, and simple editor. More documentation is available on the <xref
            href="http://www.dessci.com/en/products/mathflow/" scope="external" format="html"
              ><term>MathFlow</term> SDK</xref>website.</dd>
      </dlentry>
    </dl>
  </body>
</topic>